    Scope and Contents
SPRINGFIELD MARINE BANK PROJECT 
Bettinghaus, an employee of the Springfield Marine Bank discusses banking during the 1920's, the Depression and WWII; changes which have occurred in the profession, personnel, banking equipment and practices; working conditions, bank location, organization of departments, branch banking, the American Institute of Banking at Springfield College, the 1951 Marine Bank Centennial Celebration, and the closing of the Ridgely-Farmers National Bank in 1932. 2 tapes, 180 min., 25 pp. 
Interview by John Bucari, 1973 
